      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRACKERJACK MATT (3) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in five starts, including four wins. In the money last time at Ballarat (22.08) in a Free For All, finishing a 2.25 lengths second. Looks suited and should go close. LADY GUNAI (2) was below best at her last start when 6th at Geelong following a third place finish (22.70) there two back. Has a good record here at this journey. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Should be about the money. DIAMANTINA PEAR (1) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only one length (16.45) behind Michigan at this track. Her last run is a proven strong form reference. Deserves a win and gets her chance. KNEE DEEP (6) is one of the chances after collecting a minor prize last time.",
